SIMPLE: selfishness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Selfishness
<hw>Self"ish*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
selfish; exclusive regard to one's own interest or happiness; that
supreme self-love or self-preference which leads a person to direct his
purposes to the advancement of his own interest, power, or happiness,
without regarding those of others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Selfishness</qex>, -- a vice utterly at variance with the
happiness of him who harbors it, and, as such, condemned by
self-love.</q> <rj><qau>Sir J. Mackintosh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Self-love</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Selfism</ent>⟦br⟧
